      "cookedHtml": "<p>I recently came across this great question in one of the <a href=\"http://monday.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">monday.com</a> communities.<br />\n</p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/2/6/26d3b9526cd2d72ba08cbc166ab30302fd36c0ca.png\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/optimized/3X/2/6/26d3b9526cd2d72ba08cbc166ab30302fd36c0ca_2_690x245.png\" alt=\"image\" width=\"690\" height=\"245\" /><div class=\"meta\"><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">861×306 33.4 KB</span></div></a></div><p></p>\n<p>It’s a common scenario—someone completes a task, and you want to notify collaborators who aren’t part of your board or <a href=\"http://monday.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">monday.com</a> workspace.</p>\n<p>Here are several ways to solve this:</p>\n<h3><a name=\"p-228266-h-1-native-gmailoutlook-integration-automation-1\" class=\"anchor\" href=\"#p-228266-h-1-native-gmailoutlook-integration-automation-1\"></a><img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/white_check_mark.png?v=15\" title=\":white_check_mark:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":white_check_mark:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" /> 1. Native Gmail/Outlook Integration + Automation</h3>\n<p>You can use <a href=\"http://monday.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">monday.com</a>’s built-in Gmail or Outlook integrations.</p>\n<p><strong>Example automation:</strong></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>When status changes to “Done”, send an email to [someone@domain.com]</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/white_check_mark.png?v=15\" title=\":white_check_mark:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":white_check_mark:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" /> Easy to set up inside the platform</li>\n<li><img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/warning.png?v=15\" title=\":warning:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":warning:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" /> May result in email overload if multiple tasks are completed in a short time</li>\n</ul>\n<p></p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/b/9/b9155f6e7ba1248dc0c856b5a00a040305ec0689.png\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/b/9/b9155f6e7ba1248dc0c856b5a00a040305ec0689.png\" alt=\"image\" width=\"365\" height=\"266\" /><div class=\"meta\"><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">487×355 12.8 KB</span></div></a></div><p></p>\n<h3><a name=\"p-228266-h-2-board-email-reportshttpsmondaycommarketplacelisting10000761board-email-reports-app-digest-based-emails-2\" class=\"anchor\" href=\"#p-228266-h-2-board-email-reportshttpsmondaycommarketplacelisting10000761board-email-reports-app-digest-based-emails-2\"></a><img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/incoming_envelope.png?v=15\" title=\":incoming_envelope:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":incoming_envelope:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" /> 2. <strong><a href=\"https://monday.com/marketplace/listing/10000761/board-email-reports\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Board Email Reports</a> App</strong> (Digest-Based Emails)</h3>\n<p>Instead of triggering emails for every task, this app lets you:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Collect all tasks marked “Done” over a day, week, or custom period</li>\n<li>Send a single email with an <strong>XLS report</strong> to one or more external recipients</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Why it’s helpful:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/white_check_mark.png?v=15\" title=\":white_check_mark:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":white_check_mark:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" /> Less noise, more value—only one email per period</li>\n<li><img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/white_check_mark.png?v=15\" title=\":white_check_mark:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":white_check_mark:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" /> Reports can include direct transitions (e.g., <em>“In Progress” → “Done”</em>) or the full status journey</li>\n<li><img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/white_check_mark.png?v=15\" title=\":white_check_mark:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":white_check_mark:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" /> No need to set up email integrations—just mention the recipient emails in the automation rule</li>\n<li><img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/white_check_mark.png?v=15\" title=\":white_check_mark:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":white_check_mark:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" /> External recipients don’t need a <a href=\"http://monday.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">monday.com</a> account<br />\n<img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/3/f/3f25843ce6009143ca3a6849194963b48fa9beeb.gif\" alt=\"BER+status+transition\" width=\"690\" height=\"374\" class=\"animated\" /></li>\n</ul>\n<h3><a name=\"p-228266-h-3-use-makecom-or-zapier-3\" class=\"anchor\" href=\"#p-228266-h-3-use-makecom-or-zapier-3\"></a><img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/robot.png?v=15\" title=\":robot:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":robot:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" /> 3. Use <a href=\"http://Make.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Make.com</a> or Zapier</h3>\n<p>These tools let you build custom workflows:</p>\n<p>Trigger**: When item status changes to “Done”<br />\nAction**: Send a personalized email via Gmail, Outlook, or another service</p>\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/white_check_mark.png?v=15\" title=\":white_check_mark:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":white_check_mark:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" /> Highly customizable (format, recipients, message content)</li>\n<li><img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/warning.png?v=15\" title=\":warning:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":warning:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" /> Steeper learning curve</li>\n<li><img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/warning.png?v=15\" title=\":warning:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":warning:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" /> Setup and testing can take time</li>\n<li><img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/warning.png?v=15\" title=\":warning:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":warning:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" /> Might require technical help for more complex workflows</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/speech_balloon.png?v=15\" title=\":speech_balloon:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":speech_balloon:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" /> Have you found other ways to solve this use case? Share your thoughts or favorite tools in the comments!</p>"
